01:11:47.660 --> 01:11:50.660
of what are the purposes of education.

01:11:50.660 --> 01:11:54.120
The Greeks imagine
education in the context

01:11:54.120 --> 01:11:58.830
of the idea of the eudaimonic flourishing

01:11:58.830 --> 01:12:03.073
of human potential to
its maximum capacity.

01:12:04.700 --> 01:12:06.470
In the formative moment,

01:12:06.470 --> 01:12:11.150
when education becomes a public good

01:12:14.320 --> 01:12:19.320
when societies arrive at the
moment where public education

01:12:20.200 --> 01:12:24.760
becomes a normative ideal the world over

01:12:29.150 --> 01:12:32.960
the spirit animating that movement

01:12:32.960 --> 01:12:37.220
was the spirit of
citizens, of citizenship.

01:12:37.220 --> 01:12:39.430
And it was in fact, in the context

01:12:39.430 --> 01:12:44.430
of the last previous
wave of mass migration,

01:12:44.780 --> 01:12:49.640
when public education became
an instrument of the state

01:12:49.640 --> 01:12:52.880
to create shared experiences,

01:12:52.880 --> 01:12:57.440
to create common bonds in the citizens

01:12:57.440 --> 01:13:00.790
