about the fundamental desire

01:33:09.580 --> 01:33:11.740
the human desire for knowledge.

01:33:11.740 --> 01:33:15.670
And what role you feel passion and desire

01:33:15.670 --> 01:33:19.260
and love play in knowledge

01:33:19.260 --> 01:33:23.573
and fundamentally our desire
to exchange knowledge.

01:33:29.490 --> 01:33:30.950
- [Marcelo] We're Homo sapiens sapiens,

01:33:30.950 --> 01:33:32.936
and there you have it.

01:33:32.936 --> 01:33:33.769
(audience laughs)

01:33:33.769 --> 01:33:35.050
- [Man] Because you guys talked about food

01:33:35.050 --> 01:33:37.500
and air and I think sex, over here,

01:33:37.500 --> 01:33:39.350
at the beginning you talked about it.

01:33:39.350 --> 01:33:41.337
How does knowledge fit into that?

01:33:41.337 --> 01:33:43.170
- [Kristy] Did she talk
about sex or horniness,

01:33:43.170 --> 01:33:44.039
let's be clear?

01:33:44.039 --> 01:33:44.872
(audience laughs)

01:33:44.872 --> 01:33:45.880
- [Man] Oh, okay, sorry.

01:33:47.530 --> 01:33:49.300
Carnal knowledge, I guess.

01:33:49.300 --> 01:33:50.250
- [Marcelo] Carnal.

01:33:51.984 --> 01:33:56.984
- I think that we have a continuous desire

01:33:57.440 --> 01:34:02.440
not to say sexiness, to be in relationship

01:34:03.670 --> 01:34:08.340
to engage our environment,
whatever that is.

01:34:08.340 --> 01:34:13.060
And so I think that if knowledge
is continuously learning

01:34:13.060 --> 01:34:18.060
how to converse with the
world and the people around us

01:34:19.300 --> 01:34:20.940
at whatever scale that is

01:34:21.890 --> 01:34:26.890
it seems like that curiosity
that inquiry come, as you say,

01:34:28.520 --> 01:34:32.193
because we are part of the world.

01:34:33.640 --> 01:34:35.773
I don't even want to
say because we're human.

01:34:37.765 --> 01:34:40.210
- I think passion has a
great deal to do with it,

01:34:40.210 --> 01:34:41.780
I think love, all of those things.

01:34:41.780 --> 01:34:44.967
But really, in a certain kind of way,

01:34:44.967 --> 01:34:49.510
if there's an openness
towards observation,

01:34:49.510 --> 01:34:51.420
listening, and so on and so forth,

01:34:51.420 --> 01:34:54.630
every sensory apparatus
that we have available to us

01:34:55.950 --> 01:35:00.660
is going to make us fall towards knowing.

01:35:00.660 --> 01:35:03.710
We will fall towards knowing
in one way or another.

01:35:03.710 --> 01:35:06.040
And to me, it's that thing of when

01:35:06.040 --> 01:35:09.140
you start to recognize that
your mind can start going

01:35:09.140 --> 01:35:11.940
in all kinds of places, your
body, et cetera, et cetera.

01:35:12.830 --> 01:35:17.460
But I think, I certainly know
when someone has a passion

01:35:17.460 --> 01:35:19.510
to run out of the room
because the subject matter

01:35:19.510 --> 01:35:22.630
that they're experiencing
is making them feel nuts.

01:35:22.630 --> 01:35:25.133
My son is going through
that like madly now.

01:35:26.850 --> 01:35:29.670
There's a passion to move away from things

01:35:29.670 --> 01:35:32.210
and I think that's another
point of knowledge.

01:35:32.210 --> 01:35:36.620
It's just utterly inevitable
that within the frameworks

01:35:36.620 --> 01:35:40.830
of our belonging to life in our path

01:35:42.160 --> 01:35:44.650
knowledge is gonna fall out of our sleeves

01:35:44.650 --> 01:35:47.730
like notes on a page, you know?

01:35:47.730 --> 01:35:50.030
What we do with it is a
different kind of animal.

01:35:50.030 --> 01:35:52.770
Artistically speaking, I would say

01:35:52.770 --> 01:35:55.390
that those bodies of knowledge
associated with artists

01:35:55.390 --> 01:35:57.350
are utterly driven by passion

01:35:58.320 --> 01:36:01.840
and a willingness to
stand in acknowledgement

01:36:01.840 --> 01:36:05.660
of what is not known and
bypass a knowable outcome

01:36:05.660 --> 01:36:07.100
in service to a possibility

01:36:07.100 --> 01:36:09.720
that didn't exist without the pursuit.

01:36:09.720 --> 01:36:13.340
That requires passion and
a variety of other things.

01:36:13.340 --> 01:36:16.000
