up here in the middle.

01:36:18.240 --> 01:36:20.770
- First of all, I just
want to thank you guys

01:36:21.810 --> 01:36:23.850
for your vulnerability as a panel.

01:36:23.850 --> 01:36:25.020
I think the potential

01:36:25.020 --> 01:36:27.850
that the five of you guys have created

01:36:27.850 --> 01:36:32.110
by not cementing yourself in your fields

01:36:32.110 --> 01:36:35.830
and being open to the
vulnerability of your fields

01:36:35.830 --> 01:36:40.210
has been really awesome
for this discussion.

01:36:40.210 --> 01:36:45.210
And I'm curious how you
perceive the word amateurism.

01:36:45.410 --> 01:36:47.630
Amateur, to do something
for the love of it

01:36:48.620 --> 01:36:52.220
and how that has been, you spoke about

01:36:53.180 --> 01:36:54.700
by monetizing the peace pipe

01:36:54.700 --> 01:36:57.003
it actually takes away the power of it.

01:36:57.840 --> 01:37:00.433
As a part of this Millennial Generation,

01:37:02.790 --> 01:37:07.790
how has amateurism been used
to keep people in their place

01:37:07.810 --> 01:37:12.300
or in their lane, for
lack of a better term,

01:37:12.300 --> 01:37:17.300
especially the youth
generation throughout history,

01:37:18.060 --> 01:37:21.423
not just ours in the current moment?

01:37:23.120 --> 01:37:26.950
- I would just ask, how is amateurism

01:37:28.110 --> 01:37:30.690
a significant aspect of your experience?

01:37:30.690 --> 01:37:32.040
I'm not sure what you mean.

01:37:33.130 --> 01:37:36.773
- I think it seeps into a
lot of different fields.

01:37:37.921 --> 01:37:40.880
It the arts, definitely,

01:37:40.880 --> 01:37:44.270
also you can look at
amateur college athletics

01:37:44.270 --> 01:37:46.350
and that not being monetized,

01:37:46.350 --> 01:37:49.460
the billions of dollars that
are generated in that field

01:37:49.460 --> 01:37:52.110
is kind of more specifically
where I'm coming from.

01:37:52.110 --> 01:37:55.460
But I think the idea of amateurism, again,

01:37:55.460 --> 01:37:57.000
going off the earlier question

01:37:57.000 --> 01:38:01.040
of where love and doing
things for the love of it

01:38:01.040 --> 01:38:02.900
has been kind of stripped.

01:38:02.900 --> 01:38:05.240
You look at the rise of
B corporations, right.

01:38:05.240 --> 01:38:09.250
There's this new business
model specifically designed

01:38:09.250 --> 01:38:12.120
to say, we are a business
that actually cares

01:38:12.120 --> 01:38:14.350
when however many years ago, historically,

01:38:14.350 --> 01:38:16.460
that was just the natural component

01:38:16.460 --> 01:38:18.010
of business and transaction

01:38:18.010 --> 01:38:23.010
but now we've created an
actual, I don't know, yeah.

01:38:25.690 --> 01:38:28.789
- In Spanish, what's the word for love?

01:38:28.789 --> 01:38:32.300
(audience murmurs)
(speaks in a foreign language)

01:38:32.300 --> 01:38:34.565
Amateurism, it's the love of.

01:38:34.565 --> 01:38:36.748
- [Woman] That's what
I'm exactly getting at.

01:38:36.748 --> 01:38:41.120
- It's the love of, and to me,
all knowledge is relational.

01:38:41.120 --> 01:38:43.980
This is what 150 years
of cognitive-neuroscience

01:38:43.980 --> 01:38:45.800
finally has discovered.

01:38:45.800 --> 01:38:47.810
All knowledge is relational.

01:38:47.810 --> 01:38:51.617
It flows from the magic
word that Victoria used

01:38:53.950 --> 01:38:56.380
which is curiosity.

01:38:56.380 --> 01:38:59.770
It's the wonder of being alive.

01:38:59.770 --> 01:39:04.770
And it's the love of that
pursuit of understanding

01:39:05.550 --> 01:39:09.516
what eventually becomes
codified into knowledge

01:39:09.516 --> 01:39:14.516
that drives this perpetual
human capacity for knowing

01:39:17.350 --> 01:39:20.870
for wanting to know, for acknowledging

01:39:20.870 --> 01:39:25.040
and for the eternal magic

01:39:25.040 --> 01:39:30.040
that comes with knowing
more about the fundamental

01:39:30.068 --> 01:39:34.260
big, existential questions before us.

01:39:34.260 --> 01:39:36.640
So love is at the center.

01:39:36.640 --> 01:39:41.640
We did very fancy longitudinal
models of how kids learn

01:39:42.410 --> 01:39:44.700
and it's relational.

01:39:44.700 --> 01:39:48.040
That gets you the most for your buck

01:39:48.040 --> 01:39:52.110
if we can use that
mercantilistic metaphor.

01:39:52.110 --> 01:39:54.400
Kids learn in relationship.

01:39:54.400 --> 01:39:56.810
I always walk into a school

01:39:56.810 --> 01:40:01.143
and if the teachers are
rooting for the kids,

01:40:02.290 --> 01:40:03.970
it's a good school.

01:40:03.970 --> 01:40:05.500
It's a great school

01:40:05.500 --> 01:40:10.500
when the kids are
rooting for the teachers.

01:40:12.100 --> 01:40:14.630
Because that's true love.

01:40:14.630 --> 01:40:18.973
And there's a brief letter
that is lost in the archives.

01:40:20.370 --> 01:40:21.600
Albert Camus.

01:40:21.600 --> 01:40:23.960
So he wins a Nobel
Prize, he's a young guy,

01:40:23.960 --> 01:40:28.450
an Algerian immigrant in France.

01:40:28.450 --> 01:40:32.760
His father's not around,
his mother is mute and deaf,

01:40:32.760 --> 01:40:36.710
and he sits down, he wins a
Nobel Prize and he's in his 30s.

01:40:36.710 --> 01:40:39.280
He wrote L'Etranger,
one of the great novels.

01:40:39.280 --> 01:40:42.308
He sits down and writes
a letter to two people.

01:40:42.308 --> 01:40:46.420
To his mother and to his teacher.

01:40:46.420 --> 01:40:51.003
And that is a letter
of love to his teacher.

01:40:52.900 --> 01:40:56.510
- I would just say, in
relation to amateurism,

01:40:56.510 --> 01:40:58.400
for the love of.

01:40:58.400 --> 01:41:02.993
Protect that place inside
of your march to greatness.

01:41:03.880 --> 01:41:04.713
Utterly.

01:41:04.713 --> 01:41:08.250
Because the tyranny of
expertise can be full of traps,

01:41:08.250 --> 01:41:11.030
traps of exclusion, traps of unhappiness,

01:41:11.030 --> 01:41:12.623
traps of a variety of things.

